= \n| alias            = \u98ef\u8c37\u611b\u83dc\n| birth_date       = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year unless the exact date is already WIDELY published, as per [[WP:DOB]] -->\n| birth_place      = [[Osaka Prefecture]], [[Japan]]\n| origin           = \n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date first) -->\n| death_place      = \n| genre            = [[J-pop]], [[J-rock]]\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = [[Avex Trax]], [[WACK (music company)|WACK]]\n| associated_acts  = [[Bish (Japanese idol group)|BiSH]]\n| website          = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} or {{Official URL}} -->\n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Aina the End'''|\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9|Aina Ja Endo}}, stylized as '''AiNA THE END''', is a Japanese singer and [[Japanese idol|idol]]. Known for her hoarse singing voice, she is a founding member of the idol group [[Bish (Japanese idol group)|BiSH]].<ref name=\"profiles\">{{cite web |title=\u3010BiSH\u5927\u767e\u79d1\u3011\u300c\u697d\u5668\u3092\u6301\u305f\u306a\u3044\u30d1\u30f3\u30af\u30d0\u30f3\u30c9\u300d\u306e\u9b45\u529b\u3068\u306f\u4e00\u4f53\u4f55\u306a\u306e\u304b\uff1f \u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc6\u4eba\u3092\u5fb9\u5e95\u89e3\u8aac\uff01 |url=https://rockinon.com/news/detail/193537 |website=Rockin'on |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=ja |date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nPrior to joining BiSH, Aina the End moved to [[Tokyo]] and first worked as a singer at a nightclub in [[Shibuya]], then as a [[backup dancer|backup dancing]] unit named PARALLEL for the singer Yucat.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u98ef\u7530\u4ec1\u4e00\u90ce |title=\u3010BiSH\u3011Episode6 \u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9\u3001\u521d\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30f4\u30e5\u30fc\u300c\u79c1\u306e\u58f0\u304c\u306a\u3044\u3068\u6210\u7acb\u3057\u306a\u3044\u97f3\u697d\u306b\u51fa\u4f1a\u3044\u305f\u304b\u3063\u305f\u300d |url=https://ototoy.jp/feature/2015042205 |website=OTOTOY |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=ja |quote=22 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=PARALLEL\u304b\u3089\u7686\u69d8\u3078 |url=http://ameblo.jp/parallel5/entry-11979619893.html |website=PARALLEL Official Blog |publisher=[[Ameba (website)|Ameblo]] |accessdate=16 April 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150128080657/http://ameblo.jp/parallel5/entry-11979619893.html |archivedate=28 January 2015 |language=ja |date=20 January 2015}}</ref> Following the disbandment of [[Bis (Japanese idol group)|BiS]], Junnosuke Watanabe, the manager of the group, began auditions for a new group named BiSH in January 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u5143BiS\u30de\u30cd\u30fc\u30b8\u30e3\u30fc\u30fb\u6e21\u8fba\u6df3\u4e4b\u4ecb\u6c0f\u304cBiS\u30ea\u30d6\u30fc\u30c8\u201cBiSH\u201d\u3092\u59cb\u52d5 |url=https://www.cdjournal.com/main/news/bis/63913 |website=CD Journal |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=ja |date=14 January 2015}}</ref> In March of the same year, Aina the End was revealed as one of the five members that passed the auditions.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u5143BiS\u30de\u30cd\u30fc\u30b8\u30e3\u30fc\u624b\u639b\u3051\u308b\u65b0\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30ebBiSH\u3001\u672c\u4eba\u6b4c\u5531\u306e\u697d\u66f2\u914d\u4fe1 \u30d5\u30a9\u30ed\u30ef\u30fc4444\u4eba\u3067\u7d20\u9854\u516c\u958b |url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2050704/full/ |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=[[Oricon]] |date=27 March 2015 |language=ja}}</ref> Within the group, she was known for her husky voice, and also choreographed some songs for BiSH and [[Empire (group)|EMPiRE]].<ref name=\"profiles\"/><ref name=\"hiatus\">{{cite news |title=BiSH \u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9\u6d3b\u52d5\u4f11\u6b62\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u89e3\u7981\u300c\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u304c\u623b\u3063\u3066\u304f\u308b\u307e\u3067\u6d6e\u6c17\u3057\u306a\u3044\u3067\u4e0b\u3055\u3044\u3002\u30ad\u30e3\u30d0\u30af\u30e9\u7981\u6b62\uff01\u300d |url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/d_news/detail/45106/2 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=[[Billboard Japan]] |date=6 December 2016 |language=ja}}</ref>\n\nOn December 2016, Aina the End (and the rest of BiSH) briefly went on hiatus as she underwent surgery for [[Polyp (medicine)#Laryngeal polyps|vocal polyps]].<ref name=\"hiatus\"/><ref>{{cite news |title=BiSH\u3001\u6d99\u3053\u3089\u3048\u3057\u3070\u3057\u306e\u5225\u308c\u300c\u7121\u6575\u306a\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9\u3067\u5e30\u3063\u3066\u304d\u307e\u3059\u300d |url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/211584 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |date=2 December 2016 |language=ja}}</ref> She returned the next year for the release of the single \"Promise the Star\".<ref>{{cite web |title=BiSH\u300c\u30d7\u30ed\u30df\u30b9\u30b6\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u300d |url=https://natalie.mu/music/pp/bish04 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=ja |date=21 March 2017}}</ref> After the release of ''Wack & Scrambles Works'', a joint album of groups under the management of [[WACK (music company)|WACK]] that included the reformed BiS and [[Gang Parade]], a popularity contest was held for all participating members. The top two ranked memmebrs would release a single together under [[Avex Trax]]. Aina the End won second place behind fellow BiSH member Cent Chihiro Chicchi.<ref>{{cite web |title=VOTE!! WACK!! |url=https://ssl.avexnet.or.jp/wackscrambles/vote/ |website=[[Avex Trax]] |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=ja}}</ref> The single titled \"Yoru \u014cji to Tsuki no Hime/Kienai de\" was released on September 19, 2018, with Aina the End singing the second song.<ref>{{cite news |title=BiSH\u3001\u30bb\u30f3\u30c8\u30c1\u30d2\u30ed\u30fb\u30c1\u30c3\u30c1\u3068\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9\u304c\u30bd\u30ed\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u6c7a\u5b9a |url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/d_news/detail/66675/2 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=[[Billboard Japan]] |date=16 August 2018 |language=ja}}</ref>\n\nOutside of BiSH, Aina the End has appeared as the vocalist for other artists such as TeddyLoid,<ref name=\"teddyloid\">{{cite news |title=BiSH\u3001\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9\u304cTeddyLoid\u306e\u65b0\u30b3\u30e9\u30dcEP\u306b\u521d\u30bd\u30ed\u53ce\u9332 |url=https://www.barks.jp/news/?id=1000139244 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=BARKS |date=7 March 2017 |language=ja}}</ref> Mondo Grosso,<ref name=\"mondogrosso\">{{cite web |title=\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9(BiSH)\u3000MONDO GROSSO\u65b0\u66f2MV\u306710cm\u30cf\u30a4\u30d2\u30fc\u30eb\u5c65\u3044\u3066\u5727\u5012\u7684\u30c0\u30f3\u30b9\u62ab\u9732 |url=https://spice.eplus.jp/articles/178074 |website=Spice |publisher=Eplus |accessdate=16 April 2020 |language=ja |date=14 March 2018}}</ref> [[Marty Friedman]],<ref name=\"martyfriedman\">{{cite news |title=\u30de\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30fb\u30d5\u30ea\u30fc\u30c9\u30de\u30f3\u00d7BiSH\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9\uff06\u30bb\u30f3\u30c8\u30c1\u30d2\u30ed\u30fb\u30c1\u30c3\u30c1\u65b0\u66f2\u521d\u30aa\u30f3\u30a8\u30a2\u6c7a\u5b9a |url=https://spice.eplus.jp/articles/172731 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |date=12 February 2018 |language=ja}}</ref> [[My First Story]],<ref name=\"myfirststory\">{{cite news |title=MY FIRST STORY\u3001\u65b0\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u306e\u53ce\u9332\u66f2\u516c\u958b\u3002BiSH\u30fb\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u304c\u30dc\u30fc\u30ab\u30eb\u53c2\u52a0\u306e\u697d\u66f2\u3082 |url=https://rockinon.com/news/detail/180489 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=Rockin'on |date=1 October 2018 |language=ja}}</ref> and [[Dish (band)|DISH//]].<ref name=\"dish\">{{cite news |title=DISH//\u4e2d\u6bd2\u6027\u306b\u6e80\u3061\u305f\u65b0\u4f5c\u3067BiSH\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u3001\u30e6\u30cb\u30be\u30f3\u7530\u6df5\u3001\u3042\u3044\u307f\u3087\u3093\u3068\u30bf\u30c3\u30b0 |url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/319014 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |date=7 February 2019 |language=ja}}</ref> She also performed the outro of the 2020 television drama ''Shinitai Yoru ni Kagitte''. The song, which is titled after the series, was the first song written entirely by Aina the End.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc \u97f3\u697d \u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9 BiSH \u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300c\u6b7b\u306b\u305f\u3044\u591c\u306b\u304b\u304e\u3063\u3066\u300d\u3001\u539f\u4f5c\u5927\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3BiSH\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u304cED\u30c6\u30fc\u30de\u62c5\u5f53 \u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300c\u6b7b\u306b\u305f\u3044\u591c\u306b\u304b\u304e\u3063\u3066\u300d\u3001\u539f\u4f5c\u5927\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3BiSH\u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u304cED\u30c6\u30fc\u30de\u62c5\u5f53 |url=https://natalie.mu/music/news/366911 |accessdate=16 April 2020 |agency=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |date=12 February 2020 |language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{for|Aina The End's releases with Bish|Bish (Japanese idol group)#Discography}}\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\" | Peak chart <br> positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"3\" | Album\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | JPN\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Oricon Singles Chart|Oricon Singles]]<br><ref name=\"oricon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/658910/|title=Oricon {{pipe}} \u30a2\u30a4\u30ca\u30fb\u30b8\u30fb\u30a8\u30f3\u30c9|publisher=Oricon Music Chart|language=Japanese}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2018-10-01/|title=\"Kienaide\"}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard Japan|Hot 100]]<br><ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100|title=Billboard Japan Hot 100|publisher=Billboard Japan||language=Japanese}}\n*{{